ExecDesc.value: Microsoft Office Word Remote Code Execution(IPv6 Version)

EngDesc.value: A code execution vulnerability has been reported in Microsoft Office Word. The vulnerability is due to a memory corruption when parsing a specially crafted Word file. An attacker could possibly exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code in the context of the current user by enticing them to open a specially crafted Word document. The vendor, Microsoft, has not yet released an advisory regarding this vulnerability. TELUS Security Labs has been unable to describe the exact triggering conditions with the contractual research period.
